&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GPwSI Dermatologist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a GPwSI Dermatologist at Mid Cheshire Hospitals Foundation Trust in the Division of Diagnostics and Clinical Support Services. This is a new permanent post and an exciting opportunity to work with our well-established friendly Dermatology Team in providing dermatology services for our local population.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will participate in outpatient clinics and will undertake Dermatological diagnostic and surgical procedures as well as autonomous prescribing for patients with a wide range of dermatological conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder with report to the Consultant Dermatology team and is responsible for delivery of all aspects of the dermatology service, in line with agreed aims and objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be based at Leighton Hospital in the Dermatology Department. and will be required to undertake duties at Victoria Infirmary, Northwich (VIN) and agreed community settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is offered on a part time basis with flexibility offered in the days worked.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have full registration with the GMC including a Licence to Practise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion and further details please contact Dr Alex Harris, Consultant Dermatologist on Alex.harris@mcht.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details please contact the Medical Resourcing Department on 01270 612317 or alternatively email jack.hughes@mcht.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
